            "id": "4578290",
            "title": "QuantumScape sees increased demand outside of auto industry",
            "description": "<html><body><p class=\"MsoNormal\" data-eci=\"true\">Shares of QuantumScape (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/QS\" title=\"QuantumScape Corporation\">QS</a></span></span>) are rallying after-hours as the company improved its profitability and revealed increased interest in its battery technology from sectors outside the auto industry.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">In a <a href=\"https://ir.quantumscape.com/static-files/69410652-45ae-4ae6-9e2a-a8ddd9617aa1\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"letter to shareholders,\">letter to shareholders,</a> QuantumScape (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/QS\" title=\"QuantumScape Corporation\">QS</a>) said it is “ramping up engagements in new markets” as its high-performance solid-state design has generated “strong customer interest from global players in the military, aerospace, and government sectors.“</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">In addition, “in-rack energy storage and power delivery for AI data centers is a large and fast-growing market, and the higher energy density of our battery technology can enable increased compute density of AI data centers.”</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The company also noted the “substantial progress” on cell progress and reliability for its Eagle Line production line to enable increased production of QSE-5 cell production for the automotive industry.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">“We believe that the increased capacity of the Eagle Line will help drive a virtuous cycle of higher data volume, more rapid learning cycles, and increasing production quality.”</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">For the reported quarter, QuantumScape (<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/QS\" title=\"QuantumScape Corporation\">QS</a>) reported a loss of $0.16 per share, an improvement from a loss of $0.21 per share in the same quarter last year and a penny better than expected. Adjusted EBITDA improved from a loss of $64.6M to a loss of $63.2M.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Shares are up more than 17% in after-hours trading.</p>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
            "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/assets/og_image_1200-29b2bfe1a595477db6826bd2126c63ac2091efb7ec76347a8e7f81ba17e3de6c.png",
            "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/news/4578290-quantumscape-sees-increased-demand-outside-of-auto-industry",
            "pub_date": "2026-04-23 05:08:15",
            "source": "seekalpha",
            "kind": 1,
            "language": "en"
        },
